# Cargo / Rust build artifacts
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock

# Vendored submodule build artifacts — submodule manages its own target/.
# Submodule itself is tracked (gitlink); only its build output is local.
vendor/sce/target/

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# Mnemosyne — atomic store sidecar is workspace state; commit it (the
# audit trail lives there). GENERATED.md is derived but typically also
# committed so reviewers can read it without running the CLI.
# .atomic/  ← do NOT ignore; it IS the source of truth post Round 251.
#
# watching-zenoh hybrid carry: the 13 prose docs in mnemosyne.toml ARE
# the human-readable surface — GENERATED.md is NOT used here. Atomic
# store stays as audit-only ledger; the cascade-generated GENERATED.md
# is a byproduct of every MCP mutate primitive (MCP has no
# --no-regenerate; only mnemosyne-cli does). We don't track it.
docs/GENERATED.md

# Local Claude Code state — settings.local.json, scheduled_tasks.lock,
# transcripts, etc. Team-shared .claude/settings.json (if introduced)
# would carve out via an explicit `!.claude/settings.json` exception.
.claude/

# Activity logs (local working notes; outside mnemosyne workspace).
# Cross-session handoff lives in the atomic changelog (audit-traced);
# notes/ is a local working cache only.
notes/
